ready there. Looking at the YAML, I see it only has basic cluster settings with no security enabled, and the file realm secrets fixture shows that when the test tries to authenticate with curl using the ops-user credentials, it's hitting an issue.\n\nThe test is attempting an HTTPS connection to the cluster health endpoint with basic auth, but since TLS isn't configured on the current cluster, the request fails and returns a connection error code. The precondition loop runs through multiple attempts but ultimately exits successfully anyway, which means the index seeding never actually happens because the authentication check never succeeds.\n\nNow I need to step back and figure out what's actually happening with the cluster's security setup. Let me check if Elasticsearch is even accessible without TLS, whether authentication is required at all, and then determine the right approach to move forward.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2356,"cache_read_input_tokens":43439,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2356},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a74c9f5a-b34b-434d-9410-42f8a99cc4e4","uuid":"c3b96343-e1ee-4de0-b4b3-864af8a4c403","request_id":"req_011CcfnP7D1tcAAjdwY8gy3W"}
