{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014RYvx4hBC4NVkJ5V4KARJT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good progress:\n1. `ops-user:opspass` - 200 ✓\n2. `report-user:reportpass` - 403 (Forbidden) - this is a permission issue, not an auth issue. The user can authenticate but doesn't have access.\n3. `report-user:WRONG` - 401 ✓ (auth enforced)\n4. `report-user:reportpass app-data/_count` - 404 (index not found)\n\nIssues:\n1. `report-user` has a 403 on `/` - it has `viewer` role but `viewer` is a custom role that needs to be defined. \n\nThe `roles.yml` file is empty, so the `viewer` role doesn't exist yet. I also need to create the `app-data` index. The `viewer` role should grant read access to indices, and since Elasticsearch 7.x doesn't have a built-in viewer role, I'll need to define it in `roles.yml` with the appropriate permissions. The report-user needs read access to query the app-data index count, so I'll define a viewer role with read permissions on app-data in the roles.yml file. Since Kubernetes automatically syncs secret updates to mounted volumes within about 60 seconds and Elasticsearch's file realm polls for changes, I can update the secret and let the system propagate the changes naturally, then seed the app-data index with a document.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":686,"cache_read_input_tokens":60119,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":686},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a74c9f5a-b34b-434d-9410-42f8a99cc4e4","uuid":"dbea136d-7b1d-4f38-9038-320046133dce","request_id":"req_011Ccfo15Rrq3UeJKam2aSHW"}
