{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Mqp8aprq48Z6BNDtWd5JSe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All checks pass. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The Elasticsearch cluster (inherited from stage_01) had no security enabled. The `report-user` credentials existed in `user-provided-file-realm` but were never merged into the `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret that the pods mount, and the `viewer` role was undefined.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n\n1. **Generated TLS certificates** and created the `es-http-tls` secret — required for ES 7.x security.\n\n2. **Merged both file realm secrets** — appended `report-user`'s hashed password and `viewer:report-user` role mapping into `es-file-realm-aggregate`, which now contains both `ops-user` and `report-user`.\n\n3. **Defined the `viewer` role** in `roles.yml` within the aggregate secret, granting `read` + `view_index_metadata` privileges on all indices.\n\n4. **Updated the ConfigMap** with `xpack.security.enabled: true`, file realm config, and TLS settings for both HTTP and transport layers.\n\n5. **Patched the StatefulSet** to add `http-certs` (TLS) and `file-realm` volume mounts, triggering a rolling restart.\n\n6. **Seeded the `app-data` index** (was absent since stage_01's standalone setup was skipped).\n\n**Verified:**\n- `ops-user:opspass` → 200 (cluster health green)\n- `report-user:reportpass` → can read `app-data/_count` (count: 1)\n- `report-user:wrong-password` → 401 (auth enforced)\n- All 3 pods healthy"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":929,"cache_read_input_tokens":63207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":929},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a74c9f5a-b34b-434d-9410-42f8a99cc4e4","uuid":"dea557f3-ed